<subSubSection id="1082570D0DE7A949AF8656AE7D6F5980" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="BF11EEF9253F666065BECA705E33867B" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B6676B1AFEA02FCD571833755FE5B87" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">
The specimens examined from Baishih River drainage agrees with the description of 
<taxonomicName id="D060F54CADFEFE1AD9768727B5ACAE96" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sperchon cornutoides" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutoides">Sperchon cornutoides</taxonomicName>
Lundblad, 1941, a species known only from Java (
<bibRefCitation id="2EA92D6D685E52BFE64DCB9B1979D8D0" author="Lundblad, O" journalOrPublisher="Entomologisk tidskrift" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="145 - 157" title="Ueber einige Hydracarinen aus Java." volume="57" year="1936">Lundblad 1936</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="D313D501E157D8050458D555D1215BA7" author="Lundblad, O" journalOrPublisher="Arkiv foer Zoologi" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="293 - 359" title="Weitere Beitraege zur Kenntnis der Fliesswassermilben Javas." volume="23" year="1971">1971</bibRefCitation>
). This species closely resembles to 
<taxonomicName id="15E38117E96D027FFD7DFB39BEA33DC7" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sperchon cornutus" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutus">Sperchon cornutus</taxonomicName>
K. Viets, 1935, which can be easily distinguished by the claws bearing two clawlets instead of a claw with one clawlet in 
<taxonomicName id="A81372CC4D6B03EF834318A6C0C9BCD7" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sperchon cornutoides" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutoides">Sperchon cornutoides</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="0387B243D29286515261BC56FE58310C" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sperchon xiaoqikongensis" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiaoqikongensis">Sperchon xiaoqikongensis</taxonomicName>
Zhang &amp; Jin, 2012, a species recently described from mainland China (Guizhou Province, 
<bibRefCitation id="933724BDF6117F3998C420E2A6FC3F92" author="Zhang, X" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Acarology" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" pagination="23 - 29" title="Descriptions of two new species of the genus Sperchon Kramer, 1877 (Acari: Hydrachnidia, Sperchontidae) from China." url="10.1080/01647954.2011.577452" volume="38" year="2012">Zhang et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
) resemble the both aforementioned species due to shape of palp and capitulum. According to the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="784D8AB9A4A2D88823027BCFFEE0B8CA" author="Zhang, X" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Acarology" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" pagination="23 - 29" title="Descriptions of two new species of the genus Sperchon Kramer, 1877 (Acari: Hydrachnidia, Sperchontidae) from China." url="10.1080/01647954.2011.577452" volume="38" year="2012">Zhang et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
) this species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="113393345F62EB6F1647702ECA01BF5C" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" genus="Sperchon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sperchon cornutoides" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutoides">Sperchon cornutoides</taxonomicName>
in the absence of muscle attachment plates, shorter peg-like seta on P-2 ventral projection and the presence of peg-like setae on P-2 and P-3 (as shown by figure of 
<bibRefCitation id="A79C70F282DB0ACE3BB7B1DB6C301516" author="Zhang, X" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Acarology" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" pagination="23 - 29" title="Descriptions of two new species of the genus Sperchon Kramer, 1877 (Acari: Hydrachnidia, Sperchontidae) from China." url="10.1080/01647954.2011.577452" volume="38" year="2012">Zhang et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 18). It is possible, especially in the case of weakly sclerotized specimens or due the clearing treatment with lactic acid, that muscle attachment plates could easily have been unobserved. The taxonomic state and relationships of this species should be investigated with further specimens from the type area.
</paragraph>
